# Life-OS DNA — Entity Definitions

PURPOSE:
  Define the core entities of Life-OS.
  Make meaning stable before behavior (RNA) or UI (Expression).

RULE:
  Keep core entities minimal.
  Prefer metadata and relationships over new entity types.

---

# CORE_ENTITY_LIST

CORE_ENTITIES:
  - USER
  - AGENT
  - CATEGORY
  - VISION
  - GOAL
  - PROJECT
  - TASK
  - PHASE
  - MEMORY
  - NOTE
  - ARTIFACT

NON_CORE_ENTITIES: `(DERIVED_OR_CONFIG)`
  - XP
  - THEME
  - SCHEDULE
  - NOTIFICATION

RULE:
  Non-core items may appear later as:
    - metadata fields
    - derived views
    - configuration artifacts

---

# ENTITY DEFINITION TEMPLATE

ENTITY:
  NAME:
  PURPOSE:
  OWNS:
  OWNED_BY:
  RELATIONSHIPS:
  STATES:
  INVARIANTS:
  METADATA:
