---

# USER

ENTITY:
  NAME: USER
  PURPOSE:
    Root owner of intent, progress, and data.
  OWNS:
    - CATEGORY
    - VISION
    - GOAL
    - PROJECT
    - TASK
    - PHASE
    - MEMORY
    - NOTE
    - ARTIFACT
    - AGENT
  OWNED_BY:
    - NONE
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - USER has many entities
    - USER grants permissions to AGENT
  STATES:
    - ACTIVE
    - INACTIVE
  INVARIANTS:
    - Every entity must have an owning USER
  METADATA:
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Alex"

---

# AGENT

ENTITY:
  NAME: AGENT
  PURPOSE:
    A constrained actor that proposes or executes work
    within explicit permissions and workflows.
  OWNS:
    - ARTIFACT `(agent-generated)`
    - NOTE `(agent-generated)`
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - AGENT acts on USER-owned entities with permission
    - AGENT produces outputs that must be attributable
  STATES:
    - DISABLED
    - IDLE
    - PLANNING
    - EXECUTING
    - BLOCKED
  INVARIANTS:
    - AGENT may not act outside granted scope
    - AGENT actions must be attributable and logged
    - AGENT must not bypass invariants of target entities
  METADATA:
    - persona
    - allowed_actions
    - allowed_entities
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Planner Agent"
    - "Reflection Agent"

---

# CATEGORY

ENTITY:
  NAME: CATEGORY
  PURPOSE:
    A user-selected (or system-suggested) domain of life
    used to organize intent and progress.
  OWNS:
    - NONE
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - CATEGORY may be referenced by many VISION
    - CATEGORY may exist with zero VISION `(selected but unused)`
  STATES:
    - DRAFT
    - ACTIVE
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - CATEGORY title must be unique per USER `(optional)`
  METADATA:
    - title
    - description
    - created_at
    - updated_at
    - created_by `(USER|SYSTEM)`
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Health"
    - "Wealth"
    - "Love"
    - "Evolution"
    - "Engineering"
    - "Robotics"

---

# VISION

ENTITY:
  NAME: VISION
  PURPOSE:
    A high-level direction that guides goal selection.
    Visions may span multiple categories.
  OWNS:
    - GOAL
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - VISION belongs_to many CATEGORY
    - VISION contains many GOAL
  STATES:
    - DRAFT
    - ACTIVE
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - VISION must belong_to at least one CATEGORY
  METADATA:
    - title
    - description
    - category_ids
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Become a principal engineer with deep AI systems mastery"
    - "Improve my vitals across the board"

---

# GOAL

ENTITY:
  NAME: GOAL
  PURPOSE:
    A measurable or directional outcome under a VISION.
  OWNS:
    - PROJECT
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - GOAL belongs_to one VISION
    - GOAL contains many PROJECT
  STATES:
    - DRAFT
    - ACTIVE
    - PAUSED
    - DONE
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - GOAL must belong_to a VISION
    - DONE implies completion evidence exists `(NOTE|ARTIFACT)`
  METADATA:
    - title
    - description
    - target_date `(optional)`
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Ship Life-OS Phase 1 DNA"

---

# PROJECT

ENTITY:
  NAME: PROJECT
  PURPOSE:
    A bounded initiative in service of a GOAL.
  OWNS:
    - TASK
    - PHASE `(optional)`
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - PROJECT belongs_to one GOAL
    - PROJECT contains many TASK
  STATES:
    - DRAFT
    - ACTIVE
    - BLOCKED
    - DONE
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - PROJECT must belong_to a GOAL
    - DONE implies required TASK are DONE `(or explicitly waived)`
  METADATA:
    - title
    - description
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Life-OS DNA"

---

# TASK

ENTITY:
  NAME: TASK
  PURPOSE:
    The smallest actionable unit of work.
  OWNS:
    - NONE
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - TASK belongs_to one PROJECT
    - TASK may reference MEMORY / NOTE / ARTIFACT
  STATES:
    - BACKLOG
    - READY
    - ACTIVE
    - DONE
    - CANCELED
  INVARIANTS:
    - TASK must belong_to a PROJECT
    - DONE implies done_at exists
  METADATA:
    - title
    - description
    - priority `(optional)`
    - cadence `(optional)`
    - created_by `(USER|AGENT)`
    - origin `(USER_INPUT|AGENT_OUTPUT|SYSTEM_RULE)`
    - created_at
    - updated_at
    - done_at `(optional)`
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Define invariants for MEMORY"
    - "Daily journal entry"
    - "Create weekly summary"

---

# PHASE

ENTITY:
  NAME: PHASE
  PURPOSE:
    A structured stage of progress used to group work,
    enforce sequencing, and support synthesis.
  OWNS:
    - TASK `(as scope)`
    - ARTIFACT `(phase outputs)`
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - PHASE may belong_to PROJECT
    - PHASE has many TASK
  STATES:
    - PLANNED
    - ACTIVE
    - COMPLETE
  INVARIANTS:
    - PHASE COMPLETE implies intent/decisions/learnings artifacts exist
  METADATA:
    - name
    - description
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Phase 0 — Foundations"

---

# MEMORY

ENTITY:
  NAME: MEMORY
  PURPOSE:
    Raw captured input or observation.
    Truthy but not necessarily correct or curated.
  OWNS:
    - NONE
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - MEMORY may be referenced by NOTE or ARTIFACT
  STATES:
    - CAPTURED
    - TRIAGED
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - MEMORY must retain provenance `(source + timestamp)`
  METADATA:
    - source_type
    - source_uri `(optional)`
    - captured_at
    - created_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Journal entry"
    - "Meeting transcript"
    - "Idea dump"

---

# NOTE

ENTITY:
  NAME: NOTE
  PURPOSE:
    Human-curated interpretation or synthesis.
    Editable and reflective.
  OWNS:
    - NONE
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - NOTE may cite MEMORY
    - NOTE may produce ARTIFACT
  STATES:
    - DRAFT
    - PUBLISHED
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - NOTE must track sources when making claims `(optional)`
  METADATA:
    - title
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Insights from Phase 0"

---

# ARTIFACT

ENTITY:
  NAME: ARTIFACT
  PURPOSE:
    Stable output intended to be used, referenced, or executed.
  OWNS:
    - NONE
  OWNED_BY:
    - USER
  RELATIONSHIPS:
    - ARTIFACT may be derived_from NOTE and/or MEMORY
    - ARTIFACT may be produced_by AGENT or USER
  STATES:
    - DRAFT
    - ACTIVE
    - SUPERSEDED
    - ARCHIVED
  INVARIANTS:
    - ARTIFACT must record provenance `(creator + sources)`
    - SUPERSEDED implies replacement reference exists
  METADATA:
    - artifact_type
    - created_by `(USER|AGENT)`
    - source_ids `(optional)`
    - created_at
    - updated_at
  EXAMPLES:
    - "Daily plan"
    - "Roadmap"
    - "Dashboard"
    - "Grant draft"

---

# DERIVED OR METADATA NOTES

XP:
  - derived from entity transitions
  - not a core entity in Phase 1

THEME:
  - a rendering configuration `(Expression)`
  - stored as ARTIFACT if needed

SCHEDULE:
  - derived view over TASK + time
  - stored as ARTIFACT if needed

NOTIFICATION:
  - derived from rules over entity states
  - stored as ARTIFACT if needed

END